			"created_at": "2026-02-27T16:13:04Z",
			"updated_at": "2026-02-27T16:24:53Z",
			"body": "> If the note is in edit mode, a left-edge swipe exits edit mode (same behavior as tapping the view toggle button).\r\n\r\nI don't think we want that, because the whole point of adding the new view / edit toggle button was so that you don't have to enter the note in a view state every time anymore (I collaborated on this feature with another contributor).\r\n\r\nIf the behaviour matches that of the view toggle button, then it will save the state as view when you next enter a note. Even if it doesn't save it in the view state, this behaviour doesn't really make sense anymore, now that the way view / edit mode is changed has essentially been redesigned",
			"author_association": "COLLABORATOR",
